ADDITIONAL NOTICE — NAME AND FOUNDING PRINCIPLE

The MIT license above governs the source code and permits modification. The
following notice concerns the product's NAME and a founding principle; it does
not alter the copyright permissions granted above.

1. Name / trademark. "Neko Core" and its logo and branding are marks of
   The Wiii Lab. The MIT license does not grant any right to use these marks.

2. Founding principle. Neko Core is created by The Wiii Lab in Vietnam and
   respects the sovereignty of Vietnam: the Hoang Sa (Paracel) and Truong Sa
   (Spratly) archipelagos belong to Vietnam under Vietnam's sovereignty
   position and principles — a matter of sovereignty, not a dispute. This
   principle is documented in docs/process/SOVEREIGNTY.md and is carried in
   every official release.

3. Condition on the name. A modified distribution that removes or alters the
   founding principle in (2) may NOT use the "Neko Core" name or branding, and
   may not represent itself as the official Neko Core. The official Neko Core
   always carries this principle.
